5: I've got a favor to ask of you.
14:
Come on now. Can't you help a friend
who's down and out?
17:
...You hit that metal skull of yours and
forget what you did?
21:
What I did? I tore a tyrant off her throne.
I delivered a desolate dystopia!
26:
That's not how I remember it.
Send him home, Alk.
32:
Alk! Alk! Not even a word, and you're
shoving me off? I thought we were both
gentlemen here.
35: Well, that makes one of us.
39:
How uncommunicative can you fellows
get? Just lend me an ear—
it won't kill you.
43:
Fine. We'll listen to what you have to say,
but then will you go home?
46:
Alk. Chum. With a glare like that, you
could freeze the tropics over.
50:
Truth is, lads, I don't have a home
anymore.
55:
As you know, I've been rounding up
bugs.
60:
Yes. Well, we found those memories
rusting away in a vast sea of
nothingness... The last resting place of
data before it turns into foam.
63:
But the key Dia was given... It could
retrieve anything—ANYTHING from its
depths! Do you understand what that
means?
67: If we say yes, will you shut up?
72:
Gents, to a droid, memory IS life.
And there I was standing, with access
to every piece of data ever to pass
through air or fiber. I had found the tree
of forbidden fruit!
75:
Of course, you know how bureaucrats
are. As soon as they caught wind of this,
you couldn't dip so much as a toe into
that sea of knowledge without first
wading through a mire of red tape.
82:
Oh, I did. I snuck past them all, then
surfed that sweet web to my heart's
delight.
90:
They caught me, of course. And that,
mon amies, is how I went from hero to
zero in one night. ...Actually, zero
doesn't even cut it. I'm a wanted droid.
99:
Um... It's like he found a book of
forbidden spells, then used it for
petty evil.
102:
I see. In my world, the penalty for
that is death.
106:
Well, we aren't in your world.
Or mine, for that matter.
111:
We're in Starview Village! And HERE'S
where I intend to stay until all the
hubbub subsides.
114:
I look forward to getting to know you
lads!
118:
Hah. Hah. Rather be friends with
a werewolf.
124: It has been a while, Regis.
128:
So it has, Stella my dear.
Mind if I take a seat?
135:
You don't seem surprised by my
sudden appearance.
138: Dia told me something when we parted.
141:
Namely, that the chances of you
one day descending on Starview
were high... And that she wanted us
to take care of you.
146:
She really said that? Seems my darling
princess has outgrown her tower.
150: Are you in love with Dia?
153:
Ever heard of pulling your punches,
Stella? ...But, yes. If you promise to keep
it between us, I'll make a little
confession.
157:
She captured my heart the moment
I first heard her sing... And has kept it
ever since.
168:
No worries, Stella. I won't let anything
get me down.
172:
...She was trying to comfort me,
wasn't she?
